==English==
=== Etymology ===
{{L.}} ''[[connotare]]'', to signify beyond [[literal]] meaning, from ''[[com-#Latin|com-]]'', together, + ''[[notare#Latin|notare]]'', to mark

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊt|-əʊt]]

=== Transitive verb ===
{{en-verb|connot|ing}}

#to [[signify]] beyond its [[literal]] meaning; [[imply]] as a [[logical]] [[consequence]]
#:''Racism often '''connotes''' an underlying fear or ignorance.''
#To possess an [[inseparable]] related condition
#:''Poverty '''connotes''' hunger, which '''connotes '''crime'''.''

=== Intransitive verb ===
{{en-verb|connot|ing}}

# to express without [[overt]] reference; to imply
# to require as a logical predicate to consequence

==== Synonyms ====
*(''imply''): [[entail]], [[imply]]
*(''require as a logical predicate''): [[predicate]]

